VisitorGenerator.PluginDescription: Create fake visits and actions in Matomo. Generate fake data to populate Matomo reports.
VisitorGenerator.Warning: You are about to generate fake visits for your Matomo database.
VisitorGenerator.NotReversible: It will %1$s not%2$s be possible to easily delete these visits from the Matomo logs.
VisitorGenerator.GenerateFakeActions: This will generate at least %d fake actions on this site for each day.
VisitorGenerator.OverwriteLogFiles: You can overwrite the log files used to generate fake visits (change or add files in %s). There are log files of requests to "matomo.php" in the format "Apache combined log". Plugin developers can provide their own log files by placing '*.log' files within a 'data' directory of their plugin.
VisitorGenerator.LogImporterNote: The %1$sREADME%2$s has info on a faster tool that imports large test data in Matomo.
VisitorGenerator.AutomaticReprocess: Next time you visit the Matomo reports they will be reprocessed. This might take a few minutes.
VisitorGenerator.GeneratedVisitsFor: Generated visits for %1$s and for the last %2$s days
VisitorGenerator.ReRunArchiveScript: Please re-run the crontab './console core:archive' command to refresh the reports, as per %1$s"How to set up auto-archiving of your reports"%2$s
VisitorGenerator.CliToolUsage: The %1$sMatomo CLI tool%2$s can not only generate even more visits, but also users, websites and goals.
VisitorGenerator.ConfirmVisitorGeneration: Please tick the box to confirm visitor generation
